<dl id="n41185e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41185e">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41185e"> 185(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">H</font> turns red / when Isa <small>Black</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n41185e"><li>FW 242.19 </li><li><a href="../../flex/kd/lexkd.htm#n41185e">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/kd/l39kd.htm#n41185e">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n41185e">MS BL 47477-43</ms> </li><li>JJA 51:093 <a name="kdd0" href="../../ff/fdra/kda.htm#kdd0">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/kd/kdd0.htm#n41185e">Draft: II.1&sect;4.0</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">I <font color="green">[I.B.]</font> had a trick of drawing caricatures when I was a child, and one day <mark>when</mark> <font color="green">[L.C.]</font> was writing some letters I began to make a picture of him on the back of an envelope . I quite forget what the drawing was like&mdash;probably it was an abominable libel&mdash;but suddenly he turned round and saw what I was doing. He got up from his seat and <mark>turned very red</mark>, frightening me very much. <small> Miss Isa Bowman, <a name="IBSL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#IBSL"><cite title="source">The Story Of Lewis Carroll</cite></a>. (1899) 19</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
